theses-quebec
==============

The MIT license in LICENSE applies to the source code in this repository.

The harvested bibliographic metadata stored in data/theses.db is collected
from publicly available OAI-PMH endpoints of Quebec institutional repositories.
The metadata remains the property of each contributing institution and is
governed by their respective open-access and re-use policies.

Sources harvested
-----------------
  - Concordia University (Spectrum)        — EPrints
  - Université de Montréal (Papyrus)       — DSpace 7 / Scholaris
  - Université de Sherbrooke (Savoirs UdeS)— DSpace 7 / Scholaris
  - Bishop's University (IRis)             — DSpace 7 / Scholaris
  - UQAM (Archipel)                        — EPrints
  - UQTR (Cognitio)                        — EPrints
  - UQAC (Constellation)                   — EPrints
  - UQAR (Sémaphore)                       — EPrints
  - UQO (Dépôt institutionnel)             — EPrints
  - UQAT (Depositum)                       — EPrints
  - INRS (EspaceINRS)                      — EPrints
  - ÉTS (Espace ETS)                       — EPrints
  - TÉLUQ (R-Libre)                        — EPrints
  - Polytechnique Montréal (PolyPublie)    — EPrints
  - Université Laval (Corpus UL)           — DSpace 7
  - McGill University (eScholarship)       — Hyrax / Blacklight

Per-record provenance is preserved in the `source_id` column of the database;
the `url` column points back to the original landing page on each repository.
